# Unit Converter

A simple command-line unit converter written in Python.

## Features

- Converts between units of length (meters/feet), weight (kilograms/pounds), and temperature (Celsius/Fahrenheit)
- User selects conversion type and inputs value
- Handles invalid input gracefully

## Concepts Demonstrated

- Functions and modular code
- Input/output handling
- Conditional logic
- Exception handling

## How to Run

```bash
python unit_converter.py
```

## Possible Extensions

- Add more unit types (time, area, volume)
- Allow chain conversions (e.g., cm → m → ft)
- Support for fractional inputs

